OL,5, Teenagers whose parents smoke are four 
OL,6, times more likely to take up smoking,  
OL,7, according to a new government campaign.
OL,9,FDoctors have urged parents and other   
OL,10,Fcaregivers to give up smoking.         
OL,12,FThe Better Health Smoking campaign said
OL,13,Fthat 4.9% of teenagers whose parents   
OL,14,Fsmoke have taken up smoking, whereas   
OL,15,Fonly 1.2% of teenagers whose parents do
OL,16,Fnot smoke have taken up smoking.       
OL,18,FIn a new film issued by the NHS, health
OL,19,Fexperts discuss the link between adult 
OL,20,Fsmoking and children taking up smoking.
